Finally, the optimized ratiometric fluoroprobe was applied for DDVP detection in real-world fruit juice, fruit and vegetable samples (Table 1
                         and Table 2
                        ). The residue of DDVP in the strawberry sample was detected at 0.09 μg/g, which was in general agreement with the results from GC–MS (0.08 μg/g) (GB 23200.8-2016). No DDVP was detected in orange juice, grape juice, apple juice, tomato juice, black currant juice, apple, celery and tomato samples. Moreover, satisfactory fortification recoveries for DDVP were obtained within the range of 90.0–110.0% with RSDs of 0.7–6.3% (Table 1 and Table 2). These analytical results demonstrate the efficiency of the ratiometric fluoroprobe for DDVP detection in food matrices in terms of sensitivity, selective detection and reproducibility.
